<br>
Does it take skill to get to 60? no just time<br>
How could skill be tested in the game appart from raid encounters? Make it so only allow one group to fight<br>
How to do this?<br>
<br>
And the answer to the last question is a zone of rooms.<br>
<br>
A new zone, dungeon like, setup up to be a series of rooms (yawn sounds like a same old).<br>
<br>
The zone would have these rules<br>
1. Mobs cannot be pulled out of rooms<br>
2. Spells cannot cross room boundaries<br>
3. A room will only allow X people in it (say 6 to start with)<br>
4. Other rules could be inforced, things like the total allowable some of lvls = Y. For example X=6, Y =330. This means you can have 5 lvl 55 folks or any arangement that is 330 or less<br>
5. Other weird rules discussed in previous thread could be inforced per room, i.e. room of no healing, or room of no nuking, room of no buffs etc<br>
<br>
Basically a way of defining the challenge more precisely than it is done now. :-)<br>
<br>
